body:
Hi,

The following test fails with PHPUnit 3.5.3:
    <?php
    class MyPHPUnitTest extends PHPUnit_Framework_TestCase {
        public function testPHPUnitConsidersXMLCommentsWhenComparingDOMDocuments() {
            $doc1 = new DOMDocument();
            $doc1->loadXML('<root><!-- A comment that will be ignored --></root>');
            $doc2 = new DOMDocument();
            $doc2->loadXML('<root/>');
            $this->assertNotEquals($doc1, $doc2);
        }
    }
    ?>

Here's the output:
    There was 1 failure:

```
1) MyPHPUnitTest::testPHPUnitConsidersXMLCommentsWhenComparingDOMDocuments
Failed asserting that 
DOMDocument Object
(
)
 is not equal to 
DOMDocument Object
(
)
.
```

I would expect this test to pass because $doc1 has a comment not present in $doc2. I have tried this with assertEquals and the test passes, while I would expect it to fail.

From the API documentation (http://www.phpunit.de/manual/current/en/api.html):
    assertEquals(DOMDocument $expected, DOMDocument $actual[, string $message = ''])

```
Reports an error identified by $message if the XML documents represented by the two DOMDocument objects $expected and $actual are not equal. 
```

If I change my test above to compare the saveXML string output of the two DOMDocument's, the test does pass as expected:
    $this->assertNotEquals($doc1->saveXML(), $doc2->saveXML());

Either PHPUnit should consider comment nodes or the documentation should possibly be updated to note that it doesn't consider comment nodes.
